Coloration of juveniles in life: The light colored regions of preserved juveniles may vary from shades of white, cream, light-brown and orange in life. The dark colored regions of preserved specimens vary in shades of brown, orange-brown, reddish-brown and grayish-brown (
Fig. 16
).

